Package sep.gaia.controller.menubar

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AboutMenubarListener
    This is to implement the ActionListener Interface to check if the user presses the "About" item in the menubar to open the AboutWindow.
    CreditsClickedListener  
    ExitMenubarListener
    This is to implement the ActionListener Interface to check if the user presses the "Exit" item in the menubar to exit the program.
    HelpMenubarListener
    This is to implement the ActionListener Interface to check if the user presses the "Help" item in the menubar to open the help documentation.
    SettingsMenubarListener
    This is to implement the ActionListener Interface to check if the user presses an item in the menu bar, for example to open the SettingsWindow, exit the program or open the help documentation.
    WeatherMenubarListener
    This is to implement the ActionListener Interface to check if the user wants to enable/disable the weather overlay by pressing the item in the menubar.
    WikiMenubarListener
    This is to implement the ActionListener Interface to check if the user wants to enable/disable the availability of the wikipedia informations by pressing the item in the menubar.
